data.eligibility_criteria:
Inclusion Criteria:

* Patients with Chagas Disease Cardiomyopathy having an ICD
* At least four appropriate ICD therapies in the past six months, documented by device interrogation or medical records;
* Use of amiodarone and beta blockers in an optimized fashion;
* Life expectancy of more than one

Inclusion Criteria:

1. Paroxysmal form of AF/AFL;
2. Indications for SR recovery

Exclusion Criteria:

1. Arrhythmogenic effect of refralon, amiodarone and other antiarrhythmic drugs in history;
2. Chronic kidney disease with a decrease in glomerular filtration rate less than 30 ml / min / 1.73 m2;
